{"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit"]]},"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"enum"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"PIDFile"}],"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","text":"Overview","level":2,"anchor":"overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Each running VM writes a PID file at"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"~\/.spooktacular\/vms\/<name>.vm\/pid"},{"type":"text","text":". The file contains the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"process ID of the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"spook start"},{"type":"text","text":" process that owns the VM."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Other commands ("},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"stop"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"list"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ip"},{"type":"text","text":") read the PID file to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"determine whether a VM is running and to signal the process."}]},{"type":"heading","text":"PID File Lifecycle","level":2,"anchor":"PID-File-Lifecycle"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"spook start"},{"text":" writes the PID file before booting the VM.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"spook stop","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" reads the PID file and sends SIGTERM."}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"code":"spook start","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" installs a SIGTERM handler that gracefully","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"stops the VM, removes the PID file, and exits.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If the process crashes, the PID file becomes stale."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/PIDFile\/isProcessAlive(_:)"},{"type":"text","text":" detects stale PID files by checking"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"whether the recorded process is still running."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"orderedList"},{"type":"heading","text":"Thread Safety","level":2,"anchor":"Thread-Safety"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"All methods are static and operate on the file system. They","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"are safe to call from any thread. The PID file is a plain","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"text file containing a single integer, so reads and writes","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"are effectively atomic at the file-system level.","type":"text"}]}]}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/PIDFile","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"kind":"symbol","sections":[],"metadata":{"externalID":"s:15SpooktacularKit7PIDFileO","roleHeading":"Enumeration","role":"symbol","modules":[{"name":"SpooktacularKit"}],"symbolKind":"enum","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"PIDFile","kind":"identifier"}],"title":"PIDFile","fragments":[{"text":"enum","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"PIDFile","kind":"identifier"}]},"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"abstract":[{"text":"Manages PID files for tracking running virtual machines.","type":"text"}],"topicSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/PIDFile\/fileName"],"generated":true,"anchor":"Type-Properties","title":"Type Properties"},{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/PIDFile\/isProcessAlive(_:)","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/PIDFile\/isRunning(bundleURL:)","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/PIDFile\/read(from:)","doc:\/\/Spooktacu